Rules-Requires-Root: no

Package: alabofur
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, iproute2, kmod
Description: simple bandwidth shaper with a ufw-like UX
 alabofur caps per-interface upload/download speeds using Linux traffic
 control and ships a systemd service so the limits persist across reboot,
 with a ufw-like command UX.
 .
 Limits are stored in /etc/alabofur as INI files and re-applied on boot by
 the optional alabofur systemd service.
